---
title: Creamiest Mushroom Ravioli with Button Mushrooms and Heirloom Grape Tomatoes
description: Getting stuffed inside pasta is pretty fly for a fungi: these ravioli are packed with big umami flavors thanks to a mix of hearty mushrooms. To match all that serious ’shroom personality, we’re adding a creamy Parmesan sauce and pieces of mushroom and tomato for their veggie appeal. The result is a colorful, hearty dish that’s guaranteed to become a pasta-night classic in your home.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/creamiest-mushroom-ravioli-22b289ea.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/creamiest-mushroom-ravioli-5b9c0ed5ae08b5568a004e02-22f640ee.pdf
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamiest-mushroom-ravioli-5b9c0ed5ae08b5568a004e02
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 48 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1040 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Trim
@button mushrooms{4%ounce}, then cut into ¼-inch-thick slices. Halve and peel
@shallot{1}, then thinly slice. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise.
Pick a few @parsley{¼%ounce} leaves from stems for garnish, then finely chop the
rest of the bunch.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add mushrooms and cook, tossing, until browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add shallot,
a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste), and a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook, tossing, until shallot is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @mushroom ravioli{9%ounce} to pot. Cook until tender
and floating to the top, about ~{4%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve ½ cup
pasta cooking water, then drain.

Once shallot is softened, stir tomatoes into pan, then reduce heat to low. Stir in
@sour cream{4%tablespoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, half the
@parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, and ¼ cup pasta cooking water. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{},
chopped parsley, and more chili flakes to taste.

Add ravioli to pan, increase heat to medium, and gently toss to coat ravioli in
sauce. Cook until sauce thickens slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Add more pasta cooking water, if needed, to give sauce a loose consistency.

Divide ravioli mixture between plates, then garnish with remaining Parmesan and
reserved parsley leaves and serve.